page.title: 01SYNOPSIS
page.content: This area, with only eight dwellings, is downland and apart from Upwaltham Estate and Selhurst Park Farm it is densely wooded. The timber is mixed. Conifers are present in the Forestry Commision areas, but there is a geat deal of beech, ash and sycamore with little oak. The woodland is cared for, and populated by all kinds of wildlife, including deer. There are many foxes, and one has been a particular nuisance at Upwaltham Estate but we heard no news of badgers. They may be present however. The A285 is the main Chichester - Petworth road. The road running from Benges Cottages to Goodwood race track is narrow while the Upwaltham to East Dean road is a single track with passing places.
